<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.economist.com/printedition/displayStory.cfm?Story_ID=3861190" class="external text" title="http://www.economist.com/printedition/displayStory.cfm?Story_ID=3861190" rel="nofollow">Simpler taxes | The flat-tax revolution | Economist.com</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> Louis Kaplow. "Accuracy, Complexity, and the Income Tax," <i>Journal of Law, Economics, and Organization</i> (1998), V14 N1, p.68.<a href="http://jleo.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/reprint/14/1/61.pdf" class="external autonumber" title="http://jleo.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/reprint/14/1/61.pdf" rel="nofollow">[2]</a></li>
